# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
overview:<p>The Stormwolf is a 50-ton Clan medium OmniMech introduced in 3149, developed through a collaboration between Clan Wolf and the Fox Khanate of Clan Sea Fox. With Clan Wolf's manufacturing capacity severely strained after establishing the Wolf Empire, the touman required a compatible medium OmniMech more versatile than the specialized Skinwalker. The Fox Khanate offered their Wendigo design as a foundation, which Clan Wolf's engineers then extensively modified to meet their exacting specifications. The resulting Stormwolf was designed to balance firepower with exceptional speed, and its distinctive canid or ursid profile aligns it aesthetically with the Wulfen and Warwolf totem designs. The Stormwolf has been positioned as Clan Wolf's new medium workhorse OmniMech.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Stormwolf is built for speed above all else. Its Mynx Type Medium endo steel chassis carries a 300-rated extralight fusion engine that provides a base cruising speed of 64 kph, but the permanently installed MASC and supercharger can push the OmniMech to a remarkable 162 kph in short bursts, a velocity near-unmatched among medium 'Mechs. Six Grandthrust Mk 3 jump jets further enhance tactical mobility with 180 meters of jump capability, allowing the Stormwolf to exploit terrain and rapidly reposition between engagements.</p><p>This extraordinary mobility comes at the cost of pod space. With only fifteen tons available for mission-specific loadouts, the Stormwolf carries significantly less firepower than most medium OmniMechs, requiring its pilots to exercise finesse and careful engagement selection. A fixed Beamsplitter laser anti-missile system provides baseline protection against missile fire across all configurations.</p><p>Ten tons of Gamma Special reflective armor give the Stormwolf excellent resilience against energy weapons, though this armor type is more vulnerable to ballistic and physical attacks. The design philosophy is clear: use speed to dictate engagement terms, avoid disadvantageous confrontations, and leverage reflective armor's energy resistance to punish opponents who rely on laser-heavy loadouts. Pilots who overextend or allow themselves to be cornered, however, will find the limited weaponry and specialized armor a serious liability.</p>

deployment:<p>Alternate Configuration B prioritizes long-range striking power with an ER PPC as its primary weapon, capable of delivering punishing damage at extreme distances. A plasma cannon with one ton of ammunition and paired ER medium lasers provide layered firepower across multiple range brackets. Three additional double heat sinks bring the total to thirteen, allowing the ER PPC and plasma cannon to fire in tandem without excessive heat buildup. This configuration excels at maintaining pressure from beyond effective return fire range, fully leveraging the Stormwolf's speed to control engagement distance.</p>

history:<p>The Stormwolf was born from necessity during the tumultuous period following the establishment of the Wolf Empire. Clan Wolf's need to rapidly build up forces far exceeded the manufacturing capacity of their newly claimed territories. The introduction of the totem Wulfen and Warwolf designs had already strained the research and development facilities on Thermopolis, forcing the touman to look elsewhere for a compatible medium OmniMech that could serve a more generalist role than the Skinwalker.</p><p>The Fox Khanate of Clan Sea Fox, recognizing a commercial opportunity, offered their Wendigo OmniMech as a starting point. Clan Wolf accepted but demanded significant modifications to tailor the design to their specific requirements. The resulting development program drew upon Sea Fox manufacturing expertise and resources, with the finished Stormwolf entering production at both the CSF Kraken mobile production facility and Kallon Weapon Industries on Thermopolis.</p><p>The Stormwolf reached the Wolf touman in late 3149 and was deployed in the March offensives against Clan Jade Falcon. On Zebebelgenubi, elements of the Ninety-Third Wolf Striker Cluster used their Stormwolfs to range ahead of heavier formations, exploiting the OmniMech's extraordinary speed to catch a Jade Falcon training Star off guard on the coastal flats. The engagement demonstrated the design's intended doctrine: using speed and MASC to close rapidly, overwhelming lighter opponents before they could respond, then disengaging before reinforcements arrived.</p><p>Following their success on Zebebelgenubi, the Ninety-Third Wolf Striker followed up with a lightning assault on Gacrux, where the Stormwolf's speed contributed to the element of surprise that threw defending Republic Armed Forces troops into disarray. The defenders had no intelligence on the new OmniMech's existence, and tales of the unit's terrifying speed and the relentless tactics of its pilots spread rapidly, bolstering support for the design within the Wolf touman.</p><p>Beyond Clan Wolf's own forces, the Stormwolf has been observed in the service of the Clan Protectorate, the Rasalhague Dominion, and Wolf's Dragoons, reflecting Clan Sea Fox's willingness to sell the design to allied factions. The Stormwolf appears set to become a lasting fixture of the ilClan era's medium OmniMech roster.</p>

